Mrs. Northup. Mr. Solomon,
can i interest you with a new cravat?

229
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:55,250
Pure silk by way of the French.
- We are in need of a fresh carry all..

230
00:26:55,250 --> 00:26:57,600
For the Mrs's travels. Nothing more.

231
00:26:57,700 --> 00:27:00,750
A year's passed?
Off to Sandy Hill?

232
00:27:00,850 --> 00:27:03,200
Yes, I am.
- I have just the thing for you.

233
00:27:03,300 --> 00:27:04,877
Something to suit your style,

234
00:27:04,903 --> 00:27:07,675
but sturdy enough for the
forty miles round trip.

235
00:27:07,750 --> 00:27:09,800
It's beautiful.
- But at what price?

236
00:27:09,900 --> 00:27:11,750
We will take it.

237
00:27:11,850 --> 00:27:14,300
Children, come see what your father
has just purchased for me.

238
00:27:14,300 --> 00:27:15,700
One moment, sir
and you will be assisted.

239
00:27:15,750 --> 00:27:17,800
Mr. Parker?
- Sir?

240
00:27:17,900 --> 00:27:19,254
If we can talk about
the price ...

241
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:21,000
- If we could discuss the price;
Forgive me, Mrs. Northup.

242
00:27:21,050 --> 00:27:23,100
A customer waits.
Welcome, sir.

243
00:27:23,150 --> 00:27:25,000
Shop well, but mind your wallet.

244
00:27:25,050 --> 00:27:29,700
Ignore the gentleman's nonsense.
- Jasper!

245
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:31,800
My regrets for the intrusion, sir.

246
00:27:31,900 --> 00:27:34,700
- No intrusion.

247
00:27:37,450 --> 00:27:40,500
Good day, sir.
- Good day.

248
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:43,100
Jasper, out!

249
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:53,100
Very good.

250
00:27:53,300 --> 00:27:56,850
Let's see here ...
Eliza!

251
