if you have any regard for your own safety...

505
00:48:42,050 --> 00:48:46,050
I say, begone!

506
00:48:46,450 --> 00:48:48,300
You got no cause.

507
00:48:48,400 --> 00:48:52,050
Platt is mine, and mine to do
with as I please.

508
00:48:52,150 --> 00:48:55,650
If you touch him..

509
00:49:20,500 --> 00:49:22,850
Sam! Get the mule.

510
00:49:22,950 --> 00:49:25,950
Get Master Ford.

511
00:52:50,800 --> 00:52:54,850
I believe Tibeats is skulkin' about the premises somewhere.
He wants you dead,

512
00:52:54,950 --> 00:52:56,750
and he will attempt to have you so.

513
00:52:56,850 --> 00:52:59,250
It's no longer safe for you here.

514
00:52:59,350 --> 00:53:03,200
And I don't believe you will remain
passive if Tibeats attacks.

515
00:53:03,300 --> 00:53:06,400
I have transferred my debt to Edwin Epps.

516
00:53:06,500 --> 00:53:10,500
He will take charge of you.

517
00:53:28,950 --> 00:53:31,750
Master Ford?

518
00:53:33,000 --> 00:53:36,200
You must know that I am not a slave.

519
00:53:36,300 --> 00:53:39,400
I cannot hear that.
- Before, I came to you I was a freeman.

520
00:53:39,500 --> 00:53:42,700
I am trying to save your life!

521
00:53:43,400 --> 00:53:48,200
And... I have a debt to be mindful of.

522
00:53:48,500 --> 00:53:50,400
That, now, is to Edwin Epps.

523
00:53:50,500 --> 00:53:53,400
He is a hard man.
Prides himself on being a "nigger breaker."

524
00:53:53,500 --> 00:53:57,050
But truthfully, I could find no others
who would have you.

525
00:53:57,150 --> 00:54:00,150
You've made a reputation of yourself.

526
00:54:00,350 --> 00:54:06,350
Whatever your circumstances,
you are an exceptional nigger, Platt.

527
00:54:07,050 --> 00:54:11,050
I fear no good will come of it.

528
00:54:32,900 --> 00:54:35,800
<i>"And that servant..</i>

529
00:54:35,900 --> 00:54:39,700
<i>Which knew his Lord's will...</i>

530
00:54:39,800 --> 00:54:43,800
WHICH KNEW HIS LORD'S WILL;

531
00:54:47,300 --> 00:54:51,450
<i>and prepared not himself...</i>

532
00:54:51,650 --> 00:54:55,650
PREPARED NOT HIMSELF,

533
00:54:58,250 --> 00:55:02,050
<i>neither did according to his will,</i>

534
00:55:02,750 --> 00:55:07,300
<i>shall be beaten with many stripes...</i>

535
00:55:07,400 --> 00:55:09,500
D'ye hear that?

536
00:55:09,600 --> 00:55:12,000
"Stripes."

537
00:55:12,150 --> 00:55:14,200
That nigger that don't obey his lord -

538
00:55:14,300 --> 00:55:17,050
that's his master - d'ye see?

539
00:55:17,150 --> 00:55:22,950
- That 'ere nigger shall be beaten
with many stripes.

540
00:55:23,450 --> 00:55:27,550
Now, "many" signifies a great many.

541
00:55:27,750 --> 00:55:29,550
Forty, a hundred,

542
00:55:29,650 --> 00:55:33,650
a hundred and fifty lashes...

543
00:55:36,400 --> 00:55:39,600
That's Scripter!

544
00:55:54,250 --> 00:55:55,900
Pick that cotton.

545
00:55:56,000 --> 00:55:59,200
Move along now!

546
00:56:00,150 --> 00:56:02,000
Come on now!

547
00:56:02,100 --> 00:56:04,700
Drive dem niggers.
- Pick that cotton.

548
00:56:04,800 --> 00:56:06,750
Move along now,

549
00:56:06,800 --> 00:56:08,400
hear?

550
00:56:08,450 --> 00:56:10,650
Come on!

551
00:56:11,700 --> 00:56:14,400
Two hundred forty pounds for Bob.

552
00:56:14,500 --> 00:56:16,600
What yah got for James?

553
00:56:16,700 --> 00:56:18,950
Two hundred ninety five pounds.

554
00:56:19,050 --> 00:56:22,650
Tha's real good, boy.
Tha's real good.

555
00:56:22,750 --> 00:56:26,250
One hundred eighty two pounds for Platt.

556
00:56:26,350 --> 00:56:29,350
How much can even
an average nigger pick a day?

557
00:56:29,450 --> 00:56:34,400
Two hundred pounds.
- This nigger ain't even average.

558
00:56:34,500 --> 00:56:36,850
Five hundred twelve pounds for Patsey.

559
00:56:36,950 --> 00:56:40,150
Five hundred twelve.

560
00:56:40,500 --> 00:56:46,000
Yah men folk got no shame
lettin' Patsey out pick yah?

561
00:56:46,200 --> 00:56:51,400
The day ain't yet come
she swung lower than five hundred pounds.

562
00:56:53,250 --> 00:56:55,600
Queen of the fields, she is.

563
00:56:55,700 --> 00:56:59,250
138 pounds ...
- I ain't done, Treach.

564
00:56:59,350 --> 00:57:03,350
Ain't I owed a minute to luxuriate
on the work Patsey done?

565
00:57:03,450 --> 00:57:05,850
Yes, sir.

566
00:57:08,700 --> 00:57:11,700
Damned Queen.

567
00:57:11,800 --> 00:57:16,350
Born and bred to the field.

568
00:57:16,450 --> 00:57:19,650
A nigger among niggers,

569
00:57:20,900 --> 00:57:23,700
and God give 'er to me.

570
00:57:27,000 --> 00:57:31,000
A lesson in the rewards of righteous livin'.

571
00:57:31,850 --> 00:57:35,050
All be observant ta that.

572
00:57:35,150 --> 00:57:37,650
All!

573
00:57:37,950 --> 00:57:41,150
Now, Treach.
Now speak.

574
00:57:41,250 --> 00:57:44,750
One hundred thirty eight pounds for Phebe.

575
00:57:44,850 --> 00:57:48,700
Hit one forty five yesterday.
Pull her out.

576
00:57:48,800 --> 00:57:51,150
Two hundred six pounds for George.

577
00:57:51,250 --> 00:57:53,850
How much he pick yesterday?

578
00:57:54,200 --> 00:57:56,850
Two twenty nine.
- Not enought.

579
00:57:56,950 --> 00:58:00,350
Come on, kid.

580
00:58:00,550 --> 00:58:05,050
Come on.
- Come on, boy, move!

581
00:59:52,050 --> 00:59:54,800
Get up! Tonight we dance!
Get up!

582
00:59:54,900 --> 00:59:56,350
Bring your fiddle, Platt!
Go!

583
00:59:56,400 --> 00:59:58,550
Come on!

584
00:59:58,650 --> 01:00:01,650
Come on, Platt!
Come on!

585
01:00:12,150 --> 01:00:15,650
Come on! Where's yah merriment?
Move yer feet.

586
01:00:29,200 --> 01:00:31,450
Sell her!
- What's all this?

587
01:00:31,550 --> 01:00:34,200
You will sell the negress!

588
01:00:34,300 --> 01:00:36,200
Sell little Pats?

589
01:00:36,250 --> 01:00:39,300
She pick with more vigor
than any other nigger!

590
01:00:39,400 --> 01:00:41,950
Choose another ta go.
- No other.

591
01:00:42,050 --> 01:00:43,800
Sell her!

592
01:00:43,900 --> 01:00:46,300
I will not!

593
01:00:46,400 --> 01:00:53,400
You will remove that black bitch from this property,
'er I'll take myself back to Cheneyville.

594
01:00:56,300 --> 01:01:00,500
Back to that hog's trough
where I found you?

595
01:01:01,550 --> 01:01:07,550
Do not set yourself up against Patsey, my dear.

596
01:01:09,350 --> 01:01:16,150
'Cause I will rid myself of yah well
before I do away with her!

597
01:01:21,600 --> 01:01:23,800
Whatcha looking at?

598
01:01:23,900 --> 01:01:26,300
That damned woman!

599
01:01:26,400 --> 01:01:28,800
I won't have my mood spoiled.

600
01:01:28,900 --> 01:01:32,000
I will not.

601
01:01:32,100 --> 01:01:33,700
Dance!

602
01:01:33,800 --> 01:01:36,400
Dance, i said!

603
01:01:39,400 --> 01:01:41,000
Come on!

604
01:01:41,100 --> 01:01:45,900
Pick it up, Platt.
Play that thing, boy!

605
01:02:20,850 --> 01:02:23,700
Platt?

606
01:02:23,800 --> 01:02:26,400
Yes, Mistress.

607
01:02:27,400 --> 01:02:30,400
Can you find your way
to Bartholomew's?

608
01:02:30,500 --> 01:02:32,150
I can, ma'am.

609
01:02:32,850 --> 01:02:38,100
This is a list of goods and sundries.
You will take it to be filled and return immediately.

610
01:02:38,200 --> 01:02:40,000
Take your tag.

611
01:02:40,100 --> 01:02:44,900
Tell Bartholomew to add it to our debt.
- Yes, Mistress.

612
01:02:45,250 --> 01:02:48,250
Where yah from, Platt?

613
01:02:49,400 --> 01:02:53,100
I have told you.
- Tell me again.

614
01:02:53,200 --> 01:02:55,200
Washington.
- Who were yah Master?

615
01:02:55,300 --> 01:02:59,100
Master's name was Freeman.
- Was he a learned man?

616
01:02:59,200 --> 01:03:04,250
I suppose so.
- He learn yah ta read?

617
01:03:04,350 --> 01:03:06,950
A word here or there,

618
01:03:07,050 --> 01:03:11,100
but I have no understanding of the written text.
- Don't trouble yer self with it.

619
01:03:11,200 --> 01:03:15,800
Same as the rest, Master bought yah to work.
Tha's all.

620
01:03:15,900 --> 01:03:20,100
And any more'll earn yah a hun'red lashes.

621
01:04:24,550 --> 01:04:27,550
Come here, boy.

622
01:04:28,400 --> 01:04:30,900
Come on.

623
01:04:46,000 --> 01:04:49,050
Where are you going, boy?
- On my way to...

624
01:04:49,150 --> 01:04:53,650
Bartholomew...
Sent by Mistress Epps.

625
01:04:56,600 --> 01:04:59,550
You best get to then.

626
01:04:59,650 --> 01:05:02,850
Get that quick.

627
01:05:50,050 --> 01:05:53,000
Any trouble?
- No, ma'am.

628
01:05:53,100 --> 01:05:55,600
No trouble.

629
01:06:52,700 --> 01:06:55,950
Platt Epps, good Sunday morning.
- Good morning, Master Shaw.

630
01:06:56,050 --> 01:06:58,650
I've been sent by Master to retrieve Patsey.
May I approach?

631
01:06:58,750 --> 01:07:01,250
You may.

632
01:07:10,450 --> 01:07:12,400
Excuse me, Mistress Shaw.

633
01:07:12,500 --> 01:07:15,750
Nigger Platt.
- Patsey, Master wishes you to return.

634
01:07:15,850 --> 01:07:17,800
Sabbath day.
I's free ta roam.

635
01:07:17,900 --> 01:07:20,800
But the Master sent me running to fetch you,
and said no time should be wasted.

636
01:07:20,900 --> 01:07:24,700
Do you drink tea?
- Thank you, Mistress, but I don't dare.

637
01:07:24,800 --> 01:07:30,700
Would you knowed Massa Epps's consternation
to be any lessened wit your timely return?

638
01:07:30,800 --> 01:07:33,050
Is not it his constant condition?

639
01:07:33,150 --> 01:07:38,150
Sit. Sit and drink the tea that offered.

640
01:07:41,900 --> 01:07:45,900
What'n was Epps's concern?

641
01:07:46,000 --> 01:07:48,050
...I'd rather not say...

642
01:07:48,150 --> 01:07:50,600
L'il gossip on the Sabbath be fine.

643
01:07:50,700 --> 01:07:53,950
All things in moderation.

644
01:07:54,150 --> 01:07:57,900
As you are aware, Master Epps...

645
01:07:58,000 --> 01:08:02,500
can be a man of a hard countenance.

646
01:08:02,600 --> 01:08:04,800
You know he has ill feelings toward your husband.

647
01:08:04,900 --> 01:08:06,950
He do.

648
01:08:07,050 --> 01:08:09,100
Master Epps has somehow come to believe,

649
01:08:09,200 --> 01:08:11,800
that Master Shaw is...

650
01:08:11,900 --> 01:08:14,700
is something of a lothario.

651
01:08:14,950 --> 01:08:17,400
A misguided belief, no doubt.

652
01:08:17,500 --> 01:08:23,000
No doubt...
if not born outta truth itself.

653
01:08:23,200 --> 01:08:25,200
I meant no disrespect.

654
01:08:25,300 --> 01:08:27,250
He ain't heard you.

655
01:08:27,350 --> 01:08:31,850
I meant no disrespect to you, Mistress.

656
01:08:32,700 --> 01:08:36,850
Ha! Got no cause to worry for my sensibilities.

657
01:08:36,950 --> 01:08:41,600
I ain't felt the end of a lash in
'mo years than I cain recall.

658
01:08:41,700 --> 01:08:44,350
Ain't worked a field, neither.

659
01:08:44,450 --> 01:08:49,850
Where one time I served,
now I got others servin' me.

660
01:08:49,950 --> 01:08:55,900
The cost to my current
existence be Massa Shaw..

661
01:08:56,000 --> 01:08:59,950
Broadcasting his affections,
'n me enjoyin' his pantomime of fidelity.

662
01:09:00,050 --> 01:09:04,900
If that what keep me from
the cotton pickin' niggers, that what it be.

663
01:09:05,000 --> 01:09:10,000
A small and reasonable price to be paid 'fo sure.

664
01:09:12,850 --> 01:09:19,150
I knowed what it like to be the object
of Massa's predilections and peculiarities.

665
01:09:19,350 --> 01:09:22,000
A lusty visit in the night,

666
01:09:22,100 --> 01:09:24,900
or a visitation from the whip.

667
01:09:26,000 --> 01:09:27,750
And you take comfort, Patsey;

668
01:09:27,850 --> 01:09:30,150
the Good Lord will manage Epps.

669
01:09:30,250 --> 01:09:35,150
In His own time the Good Lord will manage dem all.

670
01:09:35,250 --> 01:09:43,250
...the curse on the Pharos is a poor example
of all that wait 'fo the plantation class.

671
01:09:46,900 --> 01:09:50,100
This is nice.

672
01:09:59,950 --> 01:10:02,100
Patsy?

673
01:10:02,200 --> 01:10:04,900
Patsey!
- Do not look in his direction. Continue on.

674
01:10:05,000 --> 01:10:07,150
Patsey...!
- Found her, Master,

675
01:10:07,250 --> 01:10:11,050
and brought her back just as instructed.

676
01:10:12,100 --> 01:10:14,400
What'd you jus now tell her?

677
01:10:14,500 --> 01:10:17,150
What'd you say to Pats?

678
01:10:17,250 --> 01:10:20,650
No words were spoken.
None of consequence.

679
01:10:20,750 --> 01:10:25,300
Lie! Damned liar!

680
01:10:25,400 --> 01:10:28,450
Saw you talkin' with 'er.

681
01:10:28,550 --> 01:10:31,050
Tell me!

682
01:10:31,700 --> 01:10:33,800
I cannot speak of what did not occur.

683
01:10:33,900 --> 01:10:37,300
I'll cut your black throat.
- Master...

684
01:10:37,400 --> 01:10:39,500
You come here!
- Master, i brought her back...

685
01:10:39,550 --> 01:10:43,050
I said come here!
- I brought her back, just like you ...

686
01:10:43,150 --> 01:10:46,700
Come here!
- Come on, let's go!

687
01:10:50,400 --> 01:10:53,400
I got her, just as instructed.

688
01:10:55,450 --> 01:10:58,450
Stay away from Patsy, boy!

689
01:11:31,150 --> 01:11:34,500
It's the Lord's day.

690
01:11:34,600 --> 01:11:38,800
Ain't nothin' Christian in us carryin' on like this.

691
01:11:44,450 --> 01:11:47,450
I concede to yah,

692
01:11:48,550 --> 01:11:51,350
but in the name of valor,

693
01:11:51,450 --> 01:11:54,950
help yer master to his feet.

694
01:11:58,950 --> 01:12:00,450
Wha's the fuss?

695
01:12:00,550 --> 01:12:04,150
Master Epps believed Patsey and me
to be in conversation when we were not.

696
01:12:04,250 --> 01:12:05,700
I tried to explain, but it lead to all this.

697
01:12:05,750 --> 01:12:07,251
What is it? Ya cain't remain the Sabbath
without her under your eye?

698
01:12:09,500 --> 01:12:11,650
Hold on...
- Ya are a no-account bastard.

699
01:12:11,750 --> 01:12:13,850
A filthy, godless heathen.

700
01:12:13,900 --> 01:12:16,650
My bed is too holy for yah ta share.

701
01:12:16,750 --> 01:12:19,050
Wha's he been tellin' yah?
- Of yer misbegotten ways.

702
01:12:19,150 --> 01:12:22,500
And he would know what of anythin'?

703
01:12:22,600 --> 01:12:25,250
I ain't even spoken with him today.

704
01:12:25,350 --> 01:12:27,650
Yah lyin' nigger, Platt.

705
01:12:27,750 --> 01:12:30,750
Have I?

706
01:12:31,200 --> 01:12:33,700
Have I?

707
01:12:35,100 --> 01:12:38,350
There; there's all the truth he got.

708
01:12:38,450 --> 01:12:41,450
Damned nigger.

709
01:14:31,500 --> 01:14:34,500
Patsy?

710
01:16:30,250 --> 01:16:33,900
A moment from the dancing.

711
01:16:34,000 --> 01:16:36,100
Come sample what I baked for y'all.

712
01:16:36,200 --> 01:16:37,850
Thank you, mistress.
- Thank you, mistress.

713
01:16:37,950 --> 01:16:39,550
Thank you, Mistress!
- Thank you, Mistress!

714
01:16:39,650 --> 01:16:43,150
Thank you, mistress.
- There'll be none for you, Patsey.

715
01:16:43,900 --> 01:16:45,700
Yah see that?

716
01:16:45,800 --> 01:16:49,300
Did yah see the
look of insolence she give me?

717
01:16:49,400 --> 01:16:53,250
Seen nothin' but her turn away.
- Are you blind or ignorant?

718
01:16:53,350 --> 01:16:55,650
It was hot, hateful scorn.

719
01:16:55,750 --> 01:16:58,400
It filled that black face.

720
01:16:58,500 --> 01:17:01,850
Yah tell me yah did'n see it, then yah choose not to look,

721
01:17:01,950 --> 01:17:03,950
or yah sayin' I lie.

722
01:17:04,050 --> 01:17:06,850
Whatever it was, it passed.

723
01:17:06,950 --> 01:17:10,300
Is that how yah are with the niggers?

724
01:17:10,400 --> 01:17:14,150
Let every ill thought fester inside 'em.

725
01:17:14,250 --> 01:17:15,800
Look at them.

726
01:17:15,900 --> 01:17:18,100
They foul with it;

727
01:17:18,200 --> 01:17:20,750
They foul with their hate.

728
01:17:20,850 --> 01:17:25,150
You let it be,
it'll come back to us in the dark a night.

729
01:17:25,250 --> 01:17:27,300
Yah want that?

730
01:17:27,400 --> 01:17:33,300
Yah want them black animals to leave us
gut like pigs in our own sleep?

731
01:17:33,400 --> 01:17:35,050
No...

732
01:17:35,150 --> 01:17:38,500
You are manless.

733
01:17:38,600 --> 01:17:41,800
A damned eunuch if ever there was.

734
01:17:41,900 --> 01:17:45,650
And if yah won't stand for me,
I'd pray you'd at least be a credit to yer own kind..

735
01:17:45,700 --> 01:17:50,300
And beat every foul thought from 'em.

736
01:17:58,300 --> 01:18:01,800
Beat it from 'em!

737
01:18:16,600 --> 01:18:18,550
Eat!

738
01:18:18,650 --> 01:18:20,900
Fill yourselves.

739
01:18:21,000 --> 01:18:24,000
...And
then we dance.

740
01:18:27,500 --> 01:18:30,700
I said, eat!

741
01:18:45,100 --> 01:18:47,850
Platt...

742
01:18:47,950 --> 01:18:51,750
Platt, you awake?

743
01:18:52,900 --> 01:18:54,900
I am.

744
01:18:55,250 --> 01:18:57,900
I have a request.

745
01:18:58,000 --> 01:19:00,800
An act of kindness.

746
01:19:03,400 --> 01:19:06,450
I secreted it from the Mistress.

747
01:19:07,750 --> 01:19:10,950
Return it!
- It yours, Platt.

748
01:19:11,700 --> 01:19:13,300
For what cause?

749
01:19:13,400 --> 01:19:16,000
All I ask:

750
01:19:16,100 --> 01:19:18,750
end my life.

751
01:19:18,850 --> 01:19:22,200
Take my body to the margin of the swamp--

752
01:19:22,300 --> 01:19:25,300
Take me by the throat.
Hold me low in the water...

753
01:19:25,400 --> 01:19:28,500
until I's still 'n without life.

754
01:19:28,600 --> 01:19:33,500
Bury me in a lonely place of dyin'.
- I will do no such thing.

755
01:19:33,600 --> 01:19:39,200
The... the gory detail with which you speak--
- I thought on it long and hard.

756
01:19:39,300 --> 01:19:41,900
It is melancholia,

757
01:19:42,000 --> 01:19:44,550
...nothing more.

758
01:19:44,650 --> 01:19:47,550
How can you fall into such despair?

759
01:19:47,650 --> 01:19:51,150
How can you not know?

760
01:19:52,700 --> 01:19:57,900
I got no comfort in this life.

761
01:19:58,950 --> 01:20:05,350
If I cain't buy mercy from yah,
I'll beg it.

762
01:20:05,450 --> 01:20:08,150
There are others.

763
01:20:08,250 --> 01:20:11,300
<i>Beg them.
- I'm begging you! - <font color=#1191CE>Why?</font></i>

764
01:20:11,400 --> 01:20:15,400
Why would you consign me to damnation
with such an un-Godly request?

765
01:20:15,450 --> 01:20:18,150
- There is God here!

766
01:20:18,250 --> 01:20:21,750
God is merciful...

767
01:20:21,950 --> 01:20:24,850
...and He forgive merciful acts.

768
01:20:24,950 --> 01:20:28,150
Won't be no hell for you.

769
01:20:29,450 --> 01:20:31,450
Do it.

770
01:20:35,900 --> 01:20:40,300
Do what I ain't got the strength ta do myself.

771
01:21:18,250 --> 01:21:20,900
It is a plague.

772
01:21:21,100 --> 01:21:26,200
Cotton worm.
- A plague! It's damn Biblical.

773
01:21:26,300 --> 01:21:30,800
Two season God done sent a plague to smite me.

774
01:21:31,550 --> 01:21:35,750
What I done that God hate me so?

775
01:21:41,100 --> 01:21:44,100
It's that Godless lot.

776
01:21:45,150 --> 01:21:46,050
They brought this on me.

777
01:21:47,150 --> 01:21:53,150
I bring 'em God's word,
and heathens they are, they brung me God's scorn.

778
01:21:55,600 --> 01:21:57,350
Damn you!

779
01:21:57,450 --> 01:21:59,700
Damn you!

780
01:21:59,800 --> 01:22:02,600
Damn all, you'all!

781
01:22:29,050 --> 01:22:32,550
Judge?
- Mr. Epps.

782
01:22:33,700 --> 01:22:38,050
I am deeply sadden to hear
about your misfortune.

783
01:22:42,250 --> 01:22:43,700
Listen up.

784
01:22:43,800 --> 01:22:46,050
Yer Judge Turner's for the season.
More if need be,

785
01:22:46,100 --> 01:22:48,250
...until my crop return.

786
01:22:48,350 --> 01:22:50,800
Yah'll bring no disrespect to me,

787
01:22:50,900 --> 01:22:53,900
and yah'll bring no biblical plagues to him.
You hear?

788
01:22:54,000 --> 01:22:56,850
Or I'll take all your skin.

789
01:22:56,950 --> 01:23:00,150
Get out.

790
01:23:50,350 --> 01:23:54,350
Get off the porch!?
Get off the porch!

791
01:24:00,500 --> 01:24:02,200
Platt is it?

792
01:24:02,300 --> 01:24:06,800
Yes, sir.
- Have you cultivated cane previously?

793
01:24:06,950 --> 01:24:10,550
No, sir. I am not.
- You take to it quite naturally.

794
01:24:10,650 --> 01:24:12,550
Are you educated?
- No, sir.

795
01:24:12,600 --> 01:24:16,400
Niggers are hired to work,
not to read and write.

796
01:24:17,500 --> 01:24:20,400
You play the fiddle?
- Yes, sir.

797
01:24:20,500 --> 01:24:22,550
Yes, I do.

798
01:24:22,850 --> 01:24:28,650
Willard Yarney, a planter up the bayou,
celebrates his anniversary in a three week's time.

799
01:24:28,750 --> 01:24:31,100
I will hold out your name to him.

800
01:24:31,200 --> 01:24:34,200
What you earn is yours to keep.

801
01:24:34,350 --> 01:24:36,000
Yes, sir.

802
01:24:36,100 --> 01:24:39,300
Mind yourself, Platt.

803
01:26:52,750 --> 01:26:56,750
Woooo!

804
01:27:01,750 --> 01:27:03,800
Joyous day it is?

805
01:27:03,900 --> 01:27:06,400
Joyous day?

806
01:27:06,500 --> 01:27:08,900
Dark times is behind us.

807
01:27:09,000 --> 01:27:13,500
Clean livin' 'n prayer
done lifted the plague.

808
01:27:14,150 --> 01:27:18,950
As thick 'n white as New England snow.

809
01:27:19,500 --> 01:27:22,900
'N now my niggers is returned to me.

810
01:27:26,150 --> 01:27:29,350
Heard Judge Turner gave you favor.

811
01:27:33,050 --> 01:27:35,100
Oh, did you beguile him, Platt,

812
01:27:35,200 --> 01:27:38,200
with your slick nigger ways?

813
01:27:40,800 --> 01:27:43,250
Well, yah won't stand idle, boy.

814
01:27:43,350 --> 01:27:46,150
Not on my land.

815
01:27:48,100 --> 01:27:51,100
Much work to do.

816
01:27:52,000 --> 01:27:54,050
Days of old long since, eh?

817
01:27:54,150 --> 01:27:56,800
Huh?

818
01:28:01,900 --> 01:28:06,065
Joyous! Joyous indeed!

819
01:28:08,600 --> 01:28:11,350
Let's go find something sweet for you. Hmm?

820
01:28:13,800 --> 01:28:16,500
Candy.
- Candy?

821
01:28:43,400 --> 01:28:46,600
George?
- 180 pounds.

822
01:28:46,700 --> 01:28:50,600
Patsey?
- Five hundred twenty pounds for Patsey.

823
01:28:50,700 --> 01:28:53,800
Tha's my girl.
Don't never let me down.

824
01:28:53,900 --> 01:28:58,400
Platt?
- One hundred sixty pounds.

825
01:28:59,300 --> 01:29:01,250
Armsby?

826
01:29:01,350 --> 01:29:04,350
Sixty four pounds.

827
01:29:08,250 --> 01:29:10,350
A good days labor would average two hundred pounds.

828
01:29:10,400 --> 01:29:13,400
Yes, sir.

829
01:29:16,300 --> 01:29:19,400
I'm sure in time y'll develope as a picker,

830
01:29:19,500 --> 01:29:22,500
but it takes effort, boy.

831
01:29:22,950 --> 01:29:25,900
Put some damn effort into it.
- Yes, sir.

832
01:29:25,950 --> 01:29:29,750
Take 'em out.
Get to whippin'.

833
01:29:34,800 --> 01:29:37,750
It's a tragedy.

834
01:29:37,850 --> 01:29:40,500
How does such come to pass?

835
01:29:40,600 --> 01:29:44,300
Working a field and picking cotton like a lowly hand.

836
01:29:44,400 --> 01:29:47,650
I'm of a damn sight better station.

837
01:29:47,750 --> 01:29:49,800
I've worked as an overseer, you know.

838
01:29:49,900 --> 01:29:53,600
I did not know, sir.
- Not "sir."

839
01:29:53,700 --> 01:29:56,450
Just Armsby.

840
01:29:56,550 --> 01:29:58,750
Not owed more than any other in the field.

841
01:29:58,800 --> 01:30:02,050
How did you get in that position,
if I may ask?

842
01:30:02,150 --> 01:30:06,150
Ask. It's just conversation.

843
01:30:06,850 --> 01:30:10,050
I became a little too dependant on the whisky,

844
01:30:10,150 --> 01:30:13,350
a little too undependable on the job.

845
01:30:13,700 --> 01:30:16,550
Before you say I'm just a sorry drunkard,

846
01:30:16,650 --> 01:30:19,150
...let me state my case:

847
01:30:19,800 --> 01:30:21,900
As reliable employment as overseeing is,

848
01:30:21,950 --> 01:30:24,850
...it's no easy chore on the spirit.

849
01:30:24,950 --> 01:30:27,850
I say no man of conscious;

850
01:30:27,950 --> 01:30:33,719
can take the lash to another human day in,
and day out without shredding at his own self.

851
01:30:33,919 --> 01:30:36,200
Takes him to a place...

852
01:30:36,300 --> 01:30:41,150
where he either makes excuses
within his mind to be unaffected...

853
01:30:41,250 --> 01:30:45,400
Or finds some way to trample his guilty sensations.

854
01:30:45,500 --> 01:30:47,200
Well, I trampled.

855
01:30:47,300 --> 01:30:50,300
And with frequency.

856
01:30:50,650 --> 01:30:56,950
I gave in to tales of wealth and prosperity;

857
01:30:57,050 --> 01:31:01,950
But such profitable outcomes are reserved
for the plantation masters.

858
01:31:02,050 --> 01:31:06,250
It's the lot of the rest of us to serve.

859
01:31:07,000 --> 01:31:10,055
Now, I want nothing more
than to earn a decent wage..

860
01:31:10,150 --> 01:31:13,350
And get myself home.

861
01:31:44,500 --> 01:31:47,350
The proceeds of my fiddling performances.

862
01:31:47,450 --> 01:31:49,700
A few picayunes,

863
01:31:49,800 --> 01:31:52,000
but all I have in the world.

864
01:31:52,100 --> 01:31:55,700
I promise them to you
if you will do me the favor I require.

865
01:31:55,800 --> 01:32:00,800
But I beg you not to expose me
if you cannot grant the request.

866
01:32:01,800 --> 01:32:02,750
What..

867
01:32:02,800 --> 01:32:06,750
What is it that you ask?
- First, your word, sir.

868
01:32:06,850 --> 01:32:09,350
On my honor.

869
01:32:09,850 --> 01:32:12,850
It is a simple enough request.

870
01:32:13,350 --> 01:32:17,150
I only that you deposit a letter
in the post office in Marksville.

871
01:32:17,200 --> 01:32:22,200
And that you keep the action
an inviolable secret forever.

872
01:32:23,950 --> 01:32:28,150
A patron is what I require, sir.

873
01:32:32,900 --> 01:32:34,600
I'll do it.

874
01:32:34,700 --> 01:32:38,300
And will accept whatever payment is offered.

875
01:32:39,950 --> 01:32:43,150
To assist you, I put my own self at risk.

876
01:32:43,250 --> 01:32:45,200
I will do so,

877
01:32:45,300 --> 01:32:49,400
but fair compensation is all I ask.

878
01:32:57,950 --> 01:32:59,950
Draw up your letter.

879
01:33:00,050 --> 01:33:04,100
We will meet again.
In two days?

880
01:33:04,200 --> 01:33:06,700
In two days.

881
01:33:08,800 --> 01:33:11,800
...Thank you.

882
01:34:27,800 --> 01:34:29,700
Well, boy.

883
01:34:29,800 --> 01:34:32,750
I understand I've got a learned nigger

884
01:34:32,850 --> 01:34:35,600
that writes letters..

885
01:34:35,700 --> 01:34:39,300
And tries to get white fellows to mail 'em.

886
01:34:45,050 --> 01:34:47,800
Well, Armsby tol' me today...

887
01:34:47,900 --> 01:34:51,400
the devil was among my niggers.

888
01:34:52,050 --> 01:34:55,150
That I had one that needed close watchin'

889
01:34:55,250 --> 01:34:58,050
or he would run away.

890
01:34:59,450 --> 01:35:02,200
When I asked him, "Why?" ...

891
01:35:02,300 --> 01:35:05,700
He said you come over to him...

892
01:35:05,800 --> 01:35:08,750
and waked him up in the middle of the night,

893
01:35:08,850 --> 01:35:12,600
and wanted him to carry a letter...

894
01:35:13,800 --> 01:35:16,600
...to Marksville.

895
01:35:20,700 --> 01:35:24,200
What have yah got to say to that?

896
01:35:25,800 --> 01:35:28,500
There is no truth in it.

897
01:35:28,600 --> 01:35:31,100
You say.

898
01:35:31,650 --> 01:35:35,150
How could I write a letter without ink or paper?

899
01:35:35,750 --> 01:35:39,750
Who am i going to write a letter.
There is no friends living as I know of.

900
01:35:40,400 --> 01:35:43,250
That Armsby...

901
01:35:43,350 --> 01:35:48,150
That Armsby is a lying drunken fellow.

902
01:35:48,800 --> 01:35:52,800
Didn't he want you to hire him for an overseer?

903
01:35:53,550 --> 01:35:56,400
That's it.

904
01:35:56,500 --> 01:35:58,550
He wants to make you believe
we're all going to run away..

905
01:35:58,650 --> 01:36:02,550
And so, you'll hire an overseer to watch us.

906
01:36:02,650 --> 01:36:05,800
He believes you are soft soap.

907
01:36:05,900 --> 01:36:09,200
He's given to such talk.

908
01:36:09,300 --> 01:36:13,500
Made this story a lie, out of whole cloth,

909
01:36:13,600 --> 01:36:17,100
'cause he wants to get a situation.

910
01:36:21,300 --> 01:36:24,800
It's all a lie, master,

911
01:36:29,200 --> 01:36:32,200
It's all a lie.

912
01:36:39,350 --> 01:36:42,350
I'll be damned.

913
01:36:47,400 --> 01:36:52,250
Were he not free and white, Platt.

914
01:36:52,350 --> 01:36:56,150
Were he not free and white.

915
01:38:25,750 --> 01:38:28,600
Edward?
Give him water!

916
01:39:12,700 --> 01:39:14,800
I just want to say something ...

917
01:39:14,900 --> 01:39:17,900
'bout Uncle Abram.

918
01:39:20,550 --> 01:39:23,100
He was a good man..

919
01:39:23,200 --> 01:39:26,700
...and always looked out for us,
ever since we were little.

920
01:39:27,000 --> 01:39:29,200
God loved him.

921
01:39:29,300 --> 01:39:32,800
God has blessed
God keep him.

922
01:39:33,000 --> 01:39:35,500
Amen.

923
01:42:00,400 --> 01:42:02,900
Wait till the end.

924
01:42:10,400 --> 01:42:12,850
Hey, Bass?

925
01:42:12,950 --> 01:42:14,400
No, no, no ...

926
01:42:14,500 --> 01:42:17,150
No shame in taking respite from the heat;

927
01:42:17,250 --> 01:42:18,950
drink, shade.

928
01:42:19,050 --> 01:42:23,150
It's ungodly for travelers.
Hearty, or otherwise.

929
01:42:26,800 --> 01:42:30,100
What's funny?
- Epps, I'm here to complete the work at hand.

930
01:42:30,200 --> 01:42:33,500
As requested
and as paid for.

931
01:42:33,600 --> 01:42:35,700
Something rubs you wrongly.

932
01:42:35,800 --> 01:42:37,500
I offer you the opportunity to speak off.

933
01:42:42,300 --> 01:42:44,869
Well you ask plainly,
so I well tell you plainly.

934
01:42:45,546 --> 01:42:47,575
What amused me just then, was..

935
01:42:47,701 --> 01:42:49,970
..Your concern for my
well being in this heat.

936
01:42:50,196 --> 01:42:51,538
When quite frankly..

937
01:42:51,664 --> 01:42:53,047
..The conditions of your labours..

938
01:42:53,073 --> 01:42:54,899
- The condition of my labour?
- It is hard!

939
01:42:54,925 --> 01:42:58,125
- What the hell?
- It's all wrong..all wrong, mr Epps.

940
01:42:58,126 --> 01:42:59,942
They ain't hired help.

941
01:43:00,568 --> 01:43:01,609
There my property.

942
01:43:02,335 --> 01:43:05,170
- You say that with pride.
- I say it as fact.

943
01:43:07,496 --> 01:43:10,505
This conversation concerns
what is fact and what's not.

944
01:43:10,931 --> 01:43:12,866
Then it must be said.

945
01:43:12,892 --> 01:43:16,101
That there is no justice,
or righteous in this slavery.

946
01:43:17,027 --> 01:43:19,209
But you do open up a interesting question..

947
01:43:20,035 --> 01:43:21,943
What right have you too your niggers?..

948
01:43:22,069 --> 01:43:24,521
..When you come down to the point?
- What right?

949
01:43:25,647 --> 01:43:28,272
I bought them, I paid for them.

950
01:43:28,998 --> 01:43:32,249
Of course you did, and the.. Law say's
you have the right to hold a nigger.

951
01:43:32,375 --> 01:43:34,713
But begging the laws pardon, It lies.

952
01:43:35,139 --> 01:43:37,750
Suppose they patch the law,
take away your liberty.

953
01:43:37,976 --> 01:43:39,401
Making you a slave.

954
01:43:39,550 --> 01:43:42,450
Suppose.
- That ain't a supposable case.

955
01:43:42,550 --> 01:43:46,200
Laws change, Epps.
Universal truths are constant.

956
01:43:46,300 --> 01:43:47,750
It is a fact,

957
01:43:47,850 --> 01:43:50,700
a plain and simle fact that what is true and right..

958
01:43:50,800 --> 01:43:55,800
Is true and right for all.
White and black alike.

959
01:43:56,550 --> 01:43:58,600
Yah compare me to a nigger, Bass?

960
01:43:58,700 --> 01:44:02,700
I only ask, in the eye's of God..
What's the difference?

961
01:44:03,500 --> 01:44:08,000
Yah might as well ask what the difference
is between a white man and a baboon.

962
01:44:08,900 --> 01:44:11,600
Now, I seen one of them critters in Orleans..

963
01:44:11,700 --> 01:44:14,350
That knowed just as much as any nigger I got.

964
01:44:14,450 --> 01:44:17,900
Listen, Eps ...
These niggers are human beings.

965
01:44:18,000 --> 01:44:20,400
If they are allowed to scale no higher than brute animals,

966
01:44:20,500 --> 01:44:24,000
you and men like you will have to answer for it.

967
01:44:24,100 --> 01:44:26,300
There's an ill, Mr. Epps.

968
01:44:26,400 --> 01:44:29,550
A fearful ill, resting on this nation--

969
01:44:29,650 --> 01:44:33,150
There will be a day of reckoning yet.

970
01:44:35,150 --> 01:44:38,000
You like to hear yourself talk, Bass,

971
01:44:38,100 --> 01:44:41,050
better than any man I know of.

972
01:44:41,150 --> 01:44:44,950
Yah'd argue that black was white, or white black

973
01:44:45,050 --> 01:44:48,250
if anybody would contradict you.

974
01:44:49,200 --> 01:44:52,650
A fine supposition if yah lived
among Yankees in New England.

975
01:44:52,750 --> 01:44:55,550
But yah don't.

976
01:44:57,900 --> 01:45:01,100
You most assuredly do not.

977
01:45:25,600 --> 01:45:28,600
I know it's somewhere in there!

978
01:45:30,450 --> 01:45:33,450
Patsey!

979
01:45:33,800 --> 01:45:35,850
Pats!

980
01:45:35,950 --> 01:45:37,950
Where is she?

981
01:45:38,050 --> 01:45:39,500
Where the Pats?

982
01:45:45,100 --> 01:45:48,250
Where is she? Where the Pats'?
Whatcha just standing there?

983
01:45:48,350 --> 01:45:50,250
We know nothin' of her, Massa.
- The hell you don't!

984
01:45:50,300 --> 01:45:52,100
We do not know anything about ...
- About what?

985
01:45:52,200 --> 01:45:53,650
Where did she go?
- I do not know.

986
01:45:53,700 --> 01:45:55,000
She run off, ain't she?
- I do not know anything.

987
01:45:55,050 --> 01:45:56,700
She ran off!
Where is it?

988
01:45:59,100 --> 01:46:01,650
You know it! You know it! You know it!
- No, no, no ...

989
01:46:01,750 --> 01:46:04,750
No i don't.

990
01:46:05,650 --> 01:46:11,150
You miserable black dogs stand like
the deef and dumb.

991
01:46:12,250 --> 01:46:14,750
Speak!

992
01:46:28,750 --> 01:46:30,950
She gone...

993
01:46:32,800 --> 01:46:35,600
My Pats gone.

994
01:46:51,650 --> 01:46:53,700
Run off. Run off, did you?

995
01:46:53,750 --> 01:46:55,700
Massa Epps--
- You miserable wench! Where you been?

996
01:46:55,750 --> 01:46:58,350
I been nowhere.
- Lies to your misdeeds!

997
01:46:58,450 --> 01:47:01,300
The Sabbath day, Massa.
I took me a walk to commune wit da Lord.

998
01:47:01,400 --> 01:47:04,800
Bring the Lord into yer deceptions?
Comin' from Shaw's plantation weren't yah?

999
01:47:04,850 --> 01:47:07,100
...No...
- Now yah speak?

1000
01:47:07,200 --> 01:47:09,350
Now that yah want to add to
'er lies yah find yer tongue!

1001
01:47:09,400 --> 01:47:12,200
I went to Massa Shaw's plantation!

1002
01:47:12,300 --> 01:47:13,950
You admit it?
- Yes.

1003
01:47:14,050 --> 01:47:16,950
Freely. And you know why.

1004
01:47:17,050 --> 01:47:20,200
I got this from Mistress Shaw.

1005
01:47:20,300 --> 01:47:24,700
Mistress Epps won't even grant me
no soap ta clean with.

1006
01:47:24,800 --> 01:47:29,300
Stink so much I make myself gag.

1007
01:47:31,500 --> 01:47:37,000
Five hundred pounds 'a cotton
day in, day out!

1008
01:47:37,150 --> 01:47:39,100
More than any man here.

1009
01:47:39,200 --> 01:47:41,300
And 'fo that I will be clean;

1010
01:47:41,400 --> 01:47:43,050
that all I ask.

1011
01:47:43,150 --> 01:47:47,600
Dis here what I went to Shaw's 'fo.

1012
01:47:47,700 --> 01:47:52,800
Liar! Liar!
- Lord knows it all!

1013
01:47:52,900 --> 01:47:58,050
You lie!
- And you blind wit yer own covetousness.

1014
01:47:58,150 --> 01:48:00,650
I don't lie, Massa.

1015
01:48:00,750 --> 01:48:04,500
If you kill me, I'll stick ta that.

1016
01:48:04,600 --> 01:48:07,000
Yeah, I'll set you down.

1017
01:48:07,100 --> 01:48:09,400
I'll learn you to go to Shaw's.

1018
01:48:09,500 --> 01:48:11,700
Treach!

1019
01:48:12,750 --> 01:48:14,300
Go fetch some line.

1020
01:48:14,400 --> 01:48:16,600
Edward?

1021
01:48:17,150 --> 01:48:21,150
Strip her.
Strike her bare 'n lash her to the post.

1022
01:48:23,600 --> 01:48:25,600
No!

1023
01:48:38,650 --> 01:48:41,650
Yah done this to yerself, Pats!

1024
01:48:52,400 --> 01:48:54,600
Do it!

1025
01:48:58,700 --> 01:49:01,700
Strike the life from her.

1026
01:49:07,100 --> 01:49:09,300
Beat her.

1027
01:49:10,050 --> 01:49:12,850
Give her the whip.
Give it all to her!

1028
01:49:13,650 --> 01:49:17,150
Plat, come here
and play it immediately!

1029
01:49:19,000 --> 01:49:21,200
Platt!

1030
01:49:22,900 --> 01:49:25,400
Come here!

1031
01:49:25,950 --> 01:49:28,950
PATSEY: I'd rather it you, Platt.

1032
01:49:29,050 --> 01:49:31,250
Strike her.

1033
01:49:31,700 --> 01:49:34,700
Strike her.

1034
01:49:55,400 --> 01:49:57,900
He pantomimes.

1035
01:49:58,000 --> 01:50:00,500
There ain't barely a welt on her.

1036
01:50:00,600 --> 01:50:03,050
That's what your niggers make of yah;

1037
01:50:03,150 --> 01:50:05,950
a fool fer the takin'.

1038
01:50:09,750 --> 01:50:12,250
Strike her, Platt!
Strike her.

1039
01:50:28,800 --> 01:50:32,700
Yah will strike her.
Yah will strike her until her flesh is rent..

1040
01:50:32,800 --> 01:50:36,900
And meat and blood flow equal,
or I will kill every nigger in my sight!

1041
01:50:37,000 --> 01:50:39,750
Do you understand me?
Strike her!

1042
01:50:39,850 --> 01:50:42,850
Strike her!

1043
01:51:24,750 --> 01:51:28,550
Until I say no more!
I ain't said nothing!

1044
01:51:33,600 --> 01:51:35,750
Give me the whip!

1045
01:51:35,850 --> 01:51:37,450
Give it!

1046
01:51:37,550 --> 01:51:39,650
Give me the whip!

1047
01:51:39,750 --> 01:51:41,750
Get up!

1048
01:52:00,350 --> 01:52:03,150
You're the devil!

1049
01:52:04,700 --> 01:52:06,700
Sooner or later...

1050
01:52:06,800 --> 01:52:14,300
somewhere in the course of eternal justice
thou shalt answer for this sin!

1051
01:52:17,450 --> 01:52:21,450
Sin? There is no sin.

1052
01:52:22,100 --> 01:52:25,900
A man does how he pleases with his property.

1053
01:52:30,800 --> 01:52:34,350
At the moment, Platt, I am of great pleasure.

1054
01:52:34,450 --> 01:52:39,450
You be goddamn careful
I don't come to wantin' to lightenin' my mood no further.

1055
01:54:56,350 --> 01:54:58,500
Master Bass,

1056
01:54:58,600 --> 01:55:02,400
I want to ask you
what part of the country you came from?

1057
01:55:02,600 --> 01:55:05,200
No part of this land.

1058
01:55:05,700 --> 01:55:08,600
I was born in Canada.

1059
01:55:08,700 --> 01:55:10,550
Now guess where that is.

1060
01:55:10,650 --> 01:55:13,400
Oh, I know where Canada is.

1061
01:55:13,500 --> 01:55:16,700
I have been there myself.

1062
01:55:20,100 --> 01:55:22,050
Montreal and

1063
01:55:22,150 --> 01:55:24,900
Kingston and Queenston
and a great many places.

1064
01:55:25,000 --> 01:55:27,200
Well traveled for a slave.

1065
01:55:27,300 --> 01:55:29,800
How came you here?

1066
01:55:30,450 --> 01:55:33,450
Master Bass,

1067
01:55:34,500 --> 01:55:38,300
if justice had been done
I never would have been here.

1068
01:55:42,700 --> 01:55:44,950
How's this?

1069
01:55:45,050 --> 01:55:47,550
Tell me all.

1070
01:55:51,500 --> 01:55:54,300
I am afraid to tell you.

1071
01:55:55,200 --> 01:55:58,700
Every word you speak is a profound secret.

1072
01:56:06,000 --> 01:56:08,300
Your story ...

1073
01:56:08,400 --> 01:56:12,600
...it is amazing, and in no good way.

1074
01:56:16,700 --> 01:56:18,450
Do you believe, sir ...

1075
01:56:18,550 --> 01:56:21,400
..in justice as you have said?

1076
01:56:21,500 --> 01:56:22,838
Yes, I do.

1077
01:56:23,038 --> 01:56:26,790
- That slavery is an evil that should befall none?

1078
01:56:29,750 --> 01:56:34,750
I believe so.
- If you truly do,

1079
01:56:35,350 --> 01:56:37,500
Then, I would ask...

1080
01:56:37,600 --> 01:56:40,100
I would beg...

1081
01:56:41,250 --> 01:56:44,350
that you write my friends in the north,

1082
01:56:44,450 --> 01:56:48,450
acquainting them with my situation..

1083
01:56:48,550 --> 01:56:51,200
And beseeching them to forward;

1084
01:56:51,300 --> 01:56:55,100
free papers.

1085
01:56:57,700 --> 01:57:01,500
It would be...

1086
01:57:02,550 --> 01:57:06,650
an unspeakable happiness;

1087
01:57:06,850 --> 01:57:10,050
To see my wife

1088
01:57:11,450 --> 01:57:15,450
and my family again.

1089
01:57:19,650 --> 01:57:23,800
I've been traveling this country for
the best part of twenty years.

1090
01:57:24,000 --> 01:57:26,800
My freedom is everything.

1091
01:57:26,900 --> 01:57:32,400
The fact that I can walk out of here tomorrow
gives me most pleasure.

1092
01:57:33,600 --> 01:57:36,800
My life doesn't mean much to anyone,

1093
01:57:37,350 --> 01:57:41,750
but it seems your life means a lot to a lot of people.

1094
01:57:42,750 --> 01:57:44,650
About what you're asking me..

1095
01:57:44,750 --> 01:57:48,250
Sir, scares me.

1096
01:57:49,450 --> 01:57:53,250
I must say, I am afraid.

1097
01:57:53,350 --> 01:57:57,150
Not just for you, but for me.

1098
01:58:04,850 --> 01:58:07,500
I will write your letter sir,

1099
01:58:07,600 --> 01:58:09,950
for if I could bring freedom,
it will be more than a pleasure.

1100
01:58:10,000 --> 01:58:12,150
...it will be my duty.

1101
01:58:12,250 --> 01:58:17,250
Now, would you be so kindly
hand me those sickles?

1102
02:00:50,150 --> 02:00:54,950
Platt...? Where is the boy called Platt?

1103
02:00:57,150 --> 02:00:59,950
Come here, boy.

1104
02:01:20,600 --> 02:01:23,800
Your name is Platt, is it?

1105
02:01:24,150 --> 02:01:26,050
Yes, sir.

1106
02:01:26,150 --> 02:01:29,350
Do you know that man?

1107
02:01:45,400 --> 02:01:47,600
Mr. Parker...?

1108
02:01:47,700 --> 02:01:49,900
Say again?

1109
02:01:51,250 --> 02:01:53,500
Mr. Parker?

1110
02:01:53,600 --> 02:01:56,250
That man received a letter
compiling many accusations.

1111
02:01:56,350 --> 02:01:58,700
You look me in the eye...

1112
02:01:58,800 --> 02:02:00,450
and on your life answer me truthfully:

1113
02:02:00,500 --> 02:02:02,300
have you any other name than Platt?

1114
02:02:02,350 --> 02:02:05,800
Solomon Northup is my name.
- Sheriff... What's all this?

1115
02:02:05,900 --> 02:02:08,650
It's official business.
- My nigga 's my job.

1116
02:02:08,750 --> 02:02:10,600
Your business waits.

1117
02:02:10,700 --> 02:02:12,850
Tell me of your family.
- I have a wife and two children.

1118
02:02:12,900 --> 02:02:15,100
...two. - What the hell?
- What were your children's names?

1119
02:02:15,150 --> 02:02:17,450
Margaret and Alonzo.
- And your wife's name before her marriage?

1120
02:02:17,500 --> 02:02:19,550
Anne Hampton.
I am who I say.

1121
02:02:19,650 --> 02:02:21,200
Where are you going, Platt?

1122
02:02:21,250 --> 02:02:23,250
Who authorized you to roam
on my property? - My mistake.

1123
02:02:24,000 --> 02:02:26,800
Platt, come back here!
Platt!

1124
02:02:26,900 --> 02:02:29,400
Come back here, boy!

1125
02:02:32,550 --> 02:02:34,850
Nah... You will unhand 'em.
Platt is my nigger!

1126
02:02:34,900 --> 02:02:37,600
He is Mr. Solomon Nortap!
- You say...

1127
02:02:37,700 --> 02:02:40,250
You come here, humiliate me
and make claims.

1128
02:02:40,300 --> 02:02:41,950
I have no doubts.
This is Solomon Northup,

1129
02:02:42,000 --> 02:02:44,350
To hell with that! My nigger,
and I'll fight you for 'em!

1130
02:02:44,450 --> 02:02:45,750
As is your right.

1131
02:02:45,800 --> 02:02:48,200
As it will be my pleasure
to bankrupt you in the courts.

1132
02:02:48,250 --> 02:02:51,050
Your decision.
Unhand him!

1133
02:02:51,550 --> 02:02:53,500
You think this is the last you'll see of me, boy?

1134
02:02:53,550 --> 02:02:55,700
It ain't.

1135
02:02:55,750 --> 02:02:58,850
I paid fairly for this nigga!
The court has the documents to prove it!

1136
02:02:58,950 --> 02:03:00,800
And we have the documents also
proving that it is free!

1137
02:03:00,850 --> 02:03:02,750
I own you!
You belong to me! Can you hear me?

1138
02:03:02,800 --> 02:03:06,400
Keep your hands off him!
- The court will take you back before sundown!

1139
02:03:06,500 --> 02:03:10,500
Platt!
- Get my horse, please.

1140
02:03:18,950 --> 02:03:21,700
Get away from him, Pats'!

1141
02:03:21,750 --> 02:03:25,950
I'll be seeing you real soon.

1142
02:03:28,550 --> 02:03:31,000
Solomon?

1143
02:05:06,800 --> 02:05:09,800
I apologize...

1144
02:05:11,000 --> 02:05:14,000
for my appearance.

1145
02:05:15,550 --> 02:05:18,350
But I have had..

1146
02:05:18,450 --> 02:05:21,200
A difficult time....

1147
02:05:21,400 --> 02:05:24,900
...these past many years

1148
02:05:29,000 --> 02:05:32,200
Margaret?

1149
02:05:35,950 --> 02:05:39,350
Alonzo?

1150
02:06:08,850 --> 02:06:11,400
Who is this?

1151
02:06:11,500 --> 02:06:14,500
This is my husband.

1152
02:06:15,100 --> 02:06:16,950
Husband ...

1153
02:06:17,050 --> 02:06:21,450
It is very good to meet you, sir.

1154
02:06:22,100 --> 02:06:24,300
We have much acquainting to do.

1155
02:06:24,400 --> 02:06:27,050
Yes, sir.

1156
02:06:27,150 --> 02:06:29,000
And this ...

1157
02:06:29,100 --> 02:06:31,850
...is your grandson.

1158
02:06:31,950 --> 02:06:36,350
Solomon Northup Staunton.

1159
02:06:45,350 --> 02:06:48,150
Solomon.

1160
02:06:56,900 --> 02:06:59,900
Forgive me.

1161
02:07:02,200 --> 02:07:07,000
There is nothing to forgive.

1162
02:07:27,800 --> 02:07:34,000
Solomon Northup was one of the few victims
of kidnapping to regain freedom from salvery.

1163
02:07:35,200 --> 02:08:38,800
Solomon brought the men responisble
for his abducation to trail

1164
02:07:40,200 --> 02:07:44,800
Unable to testify against whites in
the nation's capital,


